http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Delhi/Woman-gang-raped/article14000162.ece

A 40-year-old woman was allegedly gang-raped by two men in South Delhi’s Mehrauli on Wednesday. According to the police, the incident took place around 10 p.m., when the victim who works at a beauty parlour, near their shop went to a flat on the invitation of the accused duo (Pawan and Lovely).The two run small businesses in the area. “In her complaint, the woman told us these men called her at a flat that belonged to one of their friends, near their shop. The woman agreed to reach as they had told her they want to settle some monetary issue,” said a senior police officer. As soon as she reached, she was offered a glass of water. “But she felt sleepy and unconscious after consuming the water. It was then the men allegedly raped her and left from the flat before she regained consciousness,” said the officer. A police team was sent to the residences of Pawan and Lovely and both were arrested.